Bash: Find an example with multiple PMIDs in one axiom
$ cd /home/runner/work/efo/efo && python3 -c "                            
    import re                                                                 
                                                                              
    with open('src/ontology/efo-edit.owl', 'r') as f:                         
        content = f.read()                                                    
                                                                              
    # Find axioms with multiple PMIDs                                         
    axioms = re.findall(r'<owl:Axiom>.*?</owl:Axiom>', content, re.DOTALL)    
    for axiom in axioms:                                                      
        pmid_count = axiom.count('PMID')                                      
        if pmid_count >= 2:                                                   
            print(axiom[:500])                                                
            print('---')                                                      
            break                                                             
    "                                                                         
                                                                              
